abstract: "DTQEM v19.0 provides the exact analytical solution of the Lindblad master equation for a single qubit under continuous measurement. The model uses a fixed Hamiltonian H = (Δ/2)σ_x and a pure dephasing Lindblad operator L = √(γE_ext)σ_z. The probability to be in |1⟩ is derived in closed form: P(E,t) = ½[1 − e^{-γEt}(cos(ω₀t) + (γE/ω₀) sin(ω₀t))], ω₀ = Δ/ℏ. This solution supersedes earlier empirical fits (e.g. P ∝ (1−E)²) and reveals that the observer only affects coherence, not the system's energy. Key predictions include the decoherence time τ = 1/(γE), the critical observer strength E_crit = ω₀/γ, and the long‑time limit P(E=1)→½. The code is open‑source, numerically verified, and ready for academic use."
